INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3400','letter','1769-11-14','St Croix','','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','Edward','Stevens','','individual','','Ned, my ambition is prevalent, so that I contemn the grovelling condition of a clerk, or the like, to which my fortune condemns me, and would willingly risk my life, though not my character, to exalt my station.','ltr_alh3400.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3401','letter','1777-04-05','Morristown','NJ','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','','','','group','Committee Of The Provincial Congress','The opinion I advanced respecting the enemy\'s not moving before the beginning of May, seems to be shaken, though not entirely overthrown, by some present appearances.','ltr_alh3401.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3402','letter','1777-07-22','Smiths Clove','NY','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','','','','individual','','Your favour of the eighteenth, from Saratoga, reached me yesterday Your pronouncing Fort Edward among the other forts, indefensible, surprises me a little, as it is entirely contrary to the representations of several gentlemen of judgment','ltr_alh3402.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3403','letter','1777-09-18','','','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','John','Hancock','','individual','','I did myself the honour to write you a hasty line this evening, giving it as my opinion that the city was no longer a place of safety for you. I write you again lest that letter should not get to hand.','ltr_alh3403.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3404','letter','1777-08-04','Philadelphia','PA','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','','','','group','A Committee Of New York','The misfortune at Ticonderoga, has produced a very disagreeable alteration in our affairs, and has thrown a gloom upon the favourable prospect which the campaign previous to that event afforded.','ltr_alh3404.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3406','letter','1777-11-05','Albany','NY','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','Horatio','Gates','','individual','','By inquiry, I have learned that General Patterson\'s brigade, which is the one you propose to send, is by far the weakest of the three now here, and does not consist of more than about six hundred rank and file fit for duty.','ltr_alh3406.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3407','letter','1777-11-12','City','STATE','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','Horatio','Gates','','individual','','I have been endeavouring to collect the best idea I could of the state of things in New- York, in order the better to form a judgment of the probable reinforcement gone to General Howe.','ltr_alh3407.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3408','letter','1779-03-14','City','STATE','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','John','Jay','','individual','','This is, to raise two, three, or four battalions of negroes, with the assistance of the government of that state, by contributions from the owners, in proportion to the number they possess.','ltr_alh3408.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3409','letter','1780-00-00','Liberty Pole','','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','James','Duane','','individual','','Agreeable to your request, and my promise, I sit down to give you my ideas of the defects of our present system, and the changes necessary to save us from ruin.','ltr_alh3409.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3410','letter','1780-11-22','','','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','George','Washington','','individual','','Some time last fall, when I spoke to your excellency about going to the southward, I explained to you candidly my feelings with respect to military reputation, and how much it was my object to act a conspicuous part in some enterprise','ltr_alh3410.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3411','letter','1781-02-18','New Windsor','NY','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','Philip','Schuyler','','individual','','Since I had the pleasure of writing you last, an unexpected change has taken place in my situation. I am no longer a member of the General\'s family.','ltr_alh3411.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3412','letter','1781-04-27','De Peysters Point','NY','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','George','Washington','','individual','','It is become necessary to me to apply to your excellency, to know in what manner you foresee you will be able to employ me in the ensuing campaign. I am ready to enter into activity whenever you think proper','ltr_alh3412.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3413','letter','1781-05-02','De Peysters Point','NY','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','George','Washington','','individual','','I am extremely sorry to have embarrassed you by my late application, and that you should think there are insuperable obstacles to a compliance with it.','ltr_alh3413.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3414','letter','1781-04-30','','','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','Robert','Morris','','individual','','I was among the first who were convinced that an administration by single men was essential to the proper management of the affairs of this country.','ltr_alh3414.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3416','letter','1781-07-10','Dobbs Ferry','NY','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','Elizabeth','Schuyler','','Finding, when I came here, that nothing was said on the subject of a command, I wrote the General a letter, and enclosed him my commission.','','description','ltr_alh3416.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3417','letter','1802-08-10','New York','NY','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','','','','position','Editor Of The Evening Post','Positively and unequivocally I declare, that no such nor similar order, nor any intimation nor hint resembling it, was ever by me received, or understood to have been given.','ltr_alh3417.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3418','letter','1782-03-01','Philadelphia','PA','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','George','Washington','','individual','','The difficulties I experienced last campaign in obtaining a command, will not suffer me to make any farther application on that head.','ltr_alh3418.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3419','letter','1782-03-00','Philadelphia','PA','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','Richard','Meade','','individual','','Your heart, my Meade, is peculiarly formed for enjoyments of this kind. You have every right to be a happy husband, a happy father. You have every prospect of being so. I hope your felicity may never be interrupted.','ltr_alh3419.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3420','letter','1782-06-04','','','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','Robert','Morris','','individual','','The whole system, (if it may be so called,) of taxation in this state, is radically vicious, burthensome to the people, and unproductive to government.','ltr_alh3420.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3421','letter','1782-07-22','Poughkeepsie','NY','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','Robert','Morris','','I came to this place, and had an interview with a committee of the legislature, in which I urged the several matters contained in your instructions. I strongly represented the necessity of solid arrangements of finance','','description','ltr_alh3421.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_alh3422','letter','1782-08-10','Albany','NY','US','Alexander','Hamilton','','Richard','Meade','','individual','','nothing will interrupt our friendship. Mine for you is built on the solid basis of a full conviction that you deserve it, and that it is reciprocal, and it is the more firmly fixed, because you have few competitors.','ltr_alh3422.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Life of Alexander Hamilton by His Son, JOHN C. HAMILTON, Vol. I., 1834');
